grew to become israels largest investment firm through a series of strategic fund acquisitions it acquired a provident fund managing nis billion in assets from prisma investment house ltd in  and made its first major pension fund acquisition in  after outbidding a competitor for control of the histadrut leumit fund which managed nis billion in assets in addition vermus shut down psagots underwriting unit forbes israel ranked vermus the fourth most influential young israeli in  isa investigationsedit in  when psagot was still owned by bank leumi the israel securities authority launched an investigation into the firms dealings for suspected violations of the regulation of investment advice and investment portfolio management law  the investigation went on for a year and culminated in a raid of psagots offices and the taking in of the firms executives for questioning in late  the impetus for the investigation was a psagot fund having raised nis billion in a single day psagot founder and general manager gabriella ravid resigned along with her deputy in late  in  bank leumi agreed to pay a fine of nis million as part of a plea bargain agreement in  police arrested three senior psagot employees on charges that they were involved in manipulating the prices of government and corporate bonds in order to redound greater profits to the firm and inflate their bonuses in the years – an investigation conducted by the isa concluded with psagot agreeing to pay a fine of nis million as part of a plea bargain psagot ceo at the time roy vermus was subsequently compelled to resign from the firm after the supreme court rejected an appeal he filed against his forced ouster from the company see alsoedit economy of israel venture capital in israel referencesedit  gewirtz jason  february  israels business elite weigh irans nuclear threat cnbc retrieved  february    contact us psagot investment house retrieved  february    psagot group – israel’s largest investment house duns  retrieved  feb